description: Limit set for operation of repeatedly replacing a number by the sum of the cubes of its digits.
comments: Range of A165330; A165330(a(n))=a(n); A165331(a(n))=0. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 17 2009
mathematica: lst = {}; k = 0; While[k < 1500, a = NestWhile[Plus @@ (IntegerDigits@ #^3) &, k, Unequal, All]; If[FreeQ[lst, a], AppendTo[lst, a]]; k++]; Sort@ lst (* _Robert G. Wilson v_, Jan 19 2006, revised Jan 03 2015 *)
author: Richard Schroeppel
